author: wtopstaff
title: Sacred Heart has no trouble with Cornell, 31-6
text:
By The Associated Press October 17, 2015 3:58 pm 
FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) — Tyler Dube caught nine passes for 202 yards and a touchdown, an 80-yard fourth quarter strike from RJ Noel, to help lead Sacred Heart to a 31-6 victory over Cornell on Saturday. 
Dube’s touchdown catch was the 34th of his career, moving him past Ed Pricolo into second place on the school’s all-time list for receiving touchdowns. 
Noel completed 15 of 22 passes for 270 yards and two scores. Nate Chavious added 76 yards rushing and a touchdown for Sacred Heart (4-2). 
The Pioneers jumped out to a 10-0 lead and led 17-6 at the half. 
Josh Sweet led Cornell (0-5) with 80 yards rushing on 22 carries and one touchdown, a 3-yard second quarter run that provided the Big Red with their only points. 
Robert Somborn finished with 196 yards passing and an interception for Cornell. Topics:
